{"type":"message","id":"035f5c00","parentId":"fd83b7e4","timestamp":"2026-04-07T09:37:01.025Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the issue clearly. In the `runtime_risk_state_latest.json`, the halt is triggered by:\n- `\"strategy_max_drawdown_pct(23.3100) >= 10.0000\"` in the `gate_reasons`\n- `\"liquidity_riskoff\"` in the `liquidity_gate_reasons`\n\nBut looking at the config file `paper_live_trading_v4_3_v1.json`, I see:\n- `\"strategy_sharpe_cautious_threshold\": 0.6` — this is the Sharpe ratio threshold, not max drawdown\n- `\"portfolio_drawdown_guard_pct\": -5.0` and `\"portfolio_drawdown_halt_pct\": -6.0` — these are current portfolio drawdown thresholds\n\n\n- The `strategy_max_drawdown_pct` check isn't in the config file I'm looking at, which means it's likely being computed from the live trading system itself. I need to trace where `strategy_max_drawdown_pct` is actually defined in the codebase to understand why it's triggering the halt.","thinkingSignature":"cff549bd3082211ff92f50dc699826d40093d1a1025e8837509995561647972f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mx9ap97gecup_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"strategy_max_drawdown_pct\\|strategy_max_dd\\|strategy_max_drawdown\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".pyc\" | grep \"def \\|=\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":40146,"output":312,"cacheRead":23779,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64237,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775554610245,"responseId":"062403325cc93542882d48d3c543857e"}}
