{"type":"message","id":"45cb7df8","parentId":"819572ef","timestamp":"2026-04-07T09:37:13.388Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the key file: `generate_per_panel_runtime_risk_t05.py`. Let me look at the relevant section to understand the logic.\n\nThe key lines are:\n```python\nriskoff_pct = cfg.get(\"strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct\", 10.0)\nhalt_pct = cfg.get(\"strategy_max_drawdown_halt_pct\", 15.0)\ncurrent_dd = global_metrics.get(\"strategy_max_dd_pct\", 0.0)\n```\n\nAnd:\n```python\ngate_reasons.append(f\"strategy_max_drawdown_pct({current_dd:.4f}) >= {riskoff_pct:.4f}\")\n\n\n```\n\nSo the halt logic checks if current drawdown exceeds the riskoff threshold, and then applies additional conditions. Let me trace through the actual implementation in the risk script to see where `strategy_max_dd_pct` originates.\n\nLooking at the config, I see `portfolio_drawdown_guard_pct` and `portfolio_drawdown_halt_pct` are defined for current portfolio drawdown, but the gate is using `strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct` instead. The issue is that this threshold is being pulled from `live_trading_v1.json` based on the `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` config path, so I need to check what values are actually set there.\n\n```","thinkingSignature":"15de4c1ee7b5dfe35c5c8b4b0b0a6d04f07f8346bf96e98ec456d581f4af423b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rdxh90qzj157_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"strategy_max_drawdown\\|portfolio_drawdown\\|cautious_probe\\|allow_new_buy\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/config/live_trading_v1.json 2>/dev/null | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rdxh90qzj157_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_per_panel_runtime_risk_t05.py","offset":45,"limit":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41609,"output":434,"cacheRead":23779,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65822,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775554621294,"responseId":"0624033d64535734ca7901d503a1c661"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2e0d5dbd","parentId":"45cb7df8","timestamp":"2026-04-07T09:37:13.462Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rdxh90qzj157_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"63:    \"portfolio_drawdown_guard_pct\": -2.5,\n64:    \"portfolio_drawdown_halt_pct\": -3.5,\n68:    \"allow_new_buy_when_riskoff\": false,\n71:    \"strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct\": 10.0,\n73:    \"cautious_probe\": {"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":30,"aggregated":"63:    \"portfolio_drawdown_guard_pct\": -2.5,\n64:    \"portfolio_drawdown_halt_pct\": -3.5,\n68:    \"allow_new_buy_when_riskoff\": false,\n71:    \"strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct\": 10.0,\n73:    \"cautious_probe\": {","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775554633458}}
{"type":"message","id":"2d98892b","parentId":"2e0d5dbd","timestamp":"2026-04-07T09:37:13.467Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rdxh90qzj157_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    return None\n\ndef compute_panel_risk(global_risk: dict, profile_slug: str) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Build a per-panel runtime risk state with panel-level halt logic.\n    \n    进取方案核心修复：使用纸盘自己的真实最大回撤，\n    而不是 live_system_v1 的11年回测回撤（24.51%），\n    避免纸盘被历史回测数据错误地halt。\n    \"\"\"\n    cfg = PROFILE_RUNTIME_RISK_CONFIG.get(profile_slug, {})\n    halt_pct = cfg.get(\"strategy_max_drawdown_halt_pct\", 15.0)\n    riskoff_pct = cfg.get(\"strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct\", 10.0)\n    \n    global_metrics = global_risk.get(\"runtime_metrics\", {})\n    # 进取方案：优先用纸盘自己的真实回撤；没有则降级用全局live_system数据\n    current_dd = get_paper_real_drawdown(profile_slug)\n    if current_dd is None:\n        current_dd = global_metrics.get(\"strategy_max_dd_pct\", 0.0)\n    \n    # Panel-level halt decision\n    halt_new_buy = current_dd >= halt_pct\n    risk_off = current_dd >= riskoff_pct\n    \n    # Gate reasons\n    gate_reasons = []\n    if risk_off:\n        gate_reasons.append(f\"strategy_max_drawdown_pct({current_dd:.4f}) >= {riskoff_pct:.4f}\")\n    if halt_new_buy:\n        gate_reasons.append(f\"strategy_max_drawdown_pct({current_dd:.4f}) >= HALT_THRESHOLD({halt_pct:.4f})\")\n    \n    # Build the panel runtime risk state\n    # NOTE: The base_runtime section contains a nested runtime_truth (pre-computed\n    # from global thresholds) which overrides our panel-level fields when read\n    # by runtime_state_schema.get_runtime_truth(). We must also override that\n    # nested runtime_truth with the correct per-panel halt decision.\n    per_panel_rt = {\n        \"state\": \"risk_off\" if risk_off else (\"normal\" if not halt_new_buy else \"halted\"),\n        \"state_reason\": f\"strategy_max_drawdown_pct({current_dd:.4f}) >= {riskoff_pct:.4f}\" if risk_off else \"\",\n        \"trading_status\": \"BUY_HALT\" if halt_new_buy else \"TRADING\",\n        \"trading_status_reason\": f\"strategy_max_drawdown_pct({current_dd:.4f}) >= {halt_pct:.4f}\" if halt_new_buy else \"per_panel_ok\",\n\n[72 more lines in file. Use offset=85 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775554633463}}
{"type":"message","id":"3cb43f42","parentId":"2d98892b","timestamp":"2026-04-07T09:37:22.240Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full picture. The issue is in `generate_per_panel_runtime_risk_t05.py`:\n\n```python\ncurrent_dd = get_paper_real_drawdown(profile_slug)\nif current_dd is None:\n    current_dd = global_metrics.get(\"strategy_max_dd_pct\", 0.0)\n```\n\nSo it first tries to get the paper's real drawdown. If that fails (returns None), it falls back to the live system's OOS (out-of-sample) max drawdown from the 11-year backtest (23.31%).\n\nThe problem is that `get_paper_real_drawdown()` is returning `None`, so it falls back to `global_metrics.get(\"strategy_max_dd_pct\", 0.0)` which is the OOS backtest max drawdown of 23.31%.\n\n\nSince this exceeds the 10% riskoff threshold, it triggers `risk_off = True` and `halt_new_buy = True`. I need to check what `get_paper_real_drawdown` is actually returning and why it's not finding the paper's live trading data.","thinkingSignature":"2fe18efd6ef8609c9de8320cf1227ebd3123b4024168209456f2716f1021f619"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_01jn60suzog9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"get_paper_real_drawdown\\|paper_real_drawdown\\|paper.*drawdown\\|real_drawdown\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_per_panel_runtime_risk_t05.py 2>/dev/null | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_01jn60suzog9_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"def get_paper_real_drawdown\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/*.py 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42714,"output":376,"cacheRead":23779,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66869,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775554633468,"responseId"