{"type":"message","id":"db2ad85b","parentId":"5dfe887f","timestamp":"2026-04-07T09:37:46.070Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the problem now! The metrics files are named:\n- `paper_aggressive_trading_metrics_*.json`\n- `paper_alpha55_trading_metrics_*.json`\n- `paper_balanced_trading_metrics_*.json`\n\nBut NOT `paper_v4_3_*` or `paper_smallcap_chip_v4_3_*`. \n\nThe v4.3 paper trading profile was just added (started today 2026-04-07), but there's no metrics file for it yet. The `get_paper_real_drawdown()` function returns `None` because there's no `paper_v4_3_trading_metrics_*.json` file, so it falls back to the global live system's OOS max drawdown of 23.31%.\n \nBut wait—it's actually worse than that. The `profile_slug` being used is `smallcap_chip_v4_3_aggressive`, not just `v4_3`, so the file it's looking for is `paper_smallcap_chip_v4_3_aggressive_trading_metrics_*.json`, which definitely doesn't exist. This is the core issue: v4.3 is a brand new profile that just started paper trading today, so there's no historical metrics file to pull from yet.\n\nNow I'm trying to figure out what `PROFILE_RUNTIME_RISK_CONFIG` actually contains for this profile, and whether there's a v4_3 entry at all. The config shows `paper_live_trading_v4_3_v1.json` with `strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct` set to 10.0, but I need to check the panel_profile_registry to see how v4_3 is actually registered and what its config should be.","thinkingSignature":"48de08b8ea1d2d5651956e7b18473e51211463fe2811b913a53721c3aac8246b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0hvlvblthduo_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"v4_3\\|smallcap_chip\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/panel_profile_registry.py 2>/dev/null | head -30"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0hvlvblthduo_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-res