n        \"name\": \"严格样本外宽度盘（breadth_strict_oos）\",\n\n[40 more lines in file. Use offset=121 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775554700165}}
{"type":"message","id":"a4fea976","parentId":"95a49044","timestamp":"2026-04-07T09:38:31.372Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full picture. The `PROFILE_RUNTIME_RISK_CONFIG` only has: `exit_dual`, `exit_tight`, `alpha55`, `defensive`, `balanced`, `aggressive`, `breadth_strict_oos`, `breadth_aggressive`.\n\n`smallcap_chip_v4_3_aggressive` (the v4.3 paper profile) is NOT in the registry. So it falls back to the defensive defaults (riskoff_pct=10%, halt_pct=15%), which is way too strict for a brand new paper profile.\n\nAlso, looking at `CURRENT_PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS`, `alpha55` is listed as the current valid paper, and v4.3 isn't there either.\n\n\nThe fix is to add v4.3 to the registry with thresholds that match its strategy parameters (riskoff_pct=35%, halt_pct=40%), and register it in CURRENT_PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS so it gets picked up by the paper pipeline.\n\nBut the real problem is that even with the right thresholds, if there's no metrics file yet, the code falls back to the live system's drawdown value instead of using paper-specific data. So the issue isn't just the thresholds—it's that the metrics lookup needs to properly prefer paper live trading data over the global live system metrics when available.\n\nSince v4.3 just started today and has no historical metrics, the safest approach for a new profile is to initialize with zero drawdown and let the first real trade establish the actual risk profile, rather than borrowing the live system's 11-year backtest drawdown as a starting point.","thinkingSignature":"345c4068174f8b8a5800fb60d61a3161c7981ef5a102558410dad945f2b5580e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ylbiojfd7k2i_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/panel_profile_registry.py","offset":85,"limit":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48687,"output":405,"cacheRead":23779,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72871,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775554700170,"responseId":"0624038c087fe9c9517fd384b735d919"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5f51ab7a","parentId":"a4fea976","timestamp":"2026-04-07T09:38:31.433Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ylbiojfd7k2i_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        \"slug\": \"alpha55\",\n        \"name\": \"Alpha55 纸盘（paper_alpha55）\",\n        \"short_name\": \"Alpha55 纸盘\",\n        \"group\": \"current_paper\",\n        \"group_label\": \"当前有效纸盘\",\n    },\n]\n\nLEGACY_PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS: list[dict[str, Any]] = [\n    {\n        \"slug\": \"defensive\",\n        \"name\": \"保守纸盘（paper_defensive）\",\n        \"short_name\": \"保守纸盘\",\n        \"group\": \"legacy_paper\",\n        \"group_label\": \"历史兼容纸盘\",\n    },\n    {\n        \"slug\": \"balanced\",\n        \"name\": \"均衡纸盘（paper_balanced）\",\n        \"short_name\": \"均衡纸盘\",\n        \"group\": \"legacy_paper\",\n        \"group_label\": \"历史兼容纸盘\",\n    },\n    {\n        \"slug\": \"aggressive\",\n        \"name\": \"进取纸盘（paper_aggressive）\",\n        \"short_name\": \"进取纸盘\",\n        \"group\": \"legacy_paper\",\n        \"group_label\": \"历史兼容纸盘\",\n    },\n]\n\nBREADTH_PROFILE_SPECS: list[dict[str, Any]] = [\n    {\n        \"slug\": \"breadth_strict_oos\",\n        \"name\": \"严格样本外宽度盘（breadth_strict_oos）\",\n        \"short_name\": \"严格样本外宽度盘\",\n        \"group\": \"breadth_experimental\",\n        \"group_label\": \"宽度实验盘\",\n    },\n\n[36 more lines in file. Use offset=125 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775554711429}}
{"type":"message","id":"1700a8b6","parentId":"5f51ab7a","timestamp":"2026-04-07T09:39:11.845Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of the issue. Let me summarize:1. The v4.3 paper profile (`smallcap_chip_v4_3_aggressive`) was added to the system\n2. It's NOT in `PROFILE_RUNTIME_RISK_CONFIG` → uses defensive defaults (riskoff_pct=10%, halt_pct=15%)3. It's NOT in `CURRENT_PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS` → might not be picked up by the paper trading pipeline\n4. There's no `paper_smallcap_chip_v4_3_aggressive_trading_metrics_*.json` yet (first day)5. The fallback is `global_metrics.get(\"strategy_max_dd_pct\", 0.0)` = 23.31% from live_system_v1 OOS backtest6. \n\n23.31% exceeds both thresholds, so the system enters risk_off and halts new buys. The fix is to add v4.3 to the profile registry with thresholds matching its live trading parameters (riskoff at 35%, halt at 40%), register it in CURRENT_PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS, and handle the first-day case where no metrics exist yet by falling back to the live system's max drawdown.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the real issue: for a brand new profile with no trading history, using the 11-year out-of-sample max drawdown from a different strategy doesn't make sense. If v4.3 just started today with fresh capital and no positions, its actual drawdown should be 0% or very close to it. I need to check whether the fallback should only apply when there's genuinely no metrics file AND no trading history, rather than defaulting to the live system's historical data. a new profile with no positions and no trading history, falling back to the live system's max drawdown doesn't make sense.\n\nFor v4.3 specifically, since it's starting fresh today, the paper trading max drawdown should be 0% — there's been no trading at all. Using the live system's 23.31% as a fallback is what triggers the halt, and that's incorrect. The real issue is that the fallback logic doesn't distinguish between an established profile with historical metrics and a brand new one that's never traded.\n\nFor v4.3, I need to add it to the profile registry and set thresholds high enough that it won't halt on day one. Then I can track the actual paper trading drawdown once positions are established, rather than relying on the live system's historical drawdown as a proxy. the old strategy's OOS max drawdown is 23.31%, and since the v4.3 profile doesn't exist in the registry, it falls back to the defensive defaults which are much stricter. So the halt is triggering because of this mismatch between the old aggressive profile's loose thresholds and the defensive fallback, combined with the fact that 23.31% exceeds the 10% riskoff threshold.\n\nThe fix is straightforward: I need to register the v4.3 profile with thresholds that match its actual risk profile (30% for riskoff, 35% for halt, same as the old aggressive), and I should also register it as a current paper profile so it gets used going forward. Looking at the `CURRENT_PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS`, the `aggressive` profile is listed there, so the system is using that one. I need to add the v4.3 config to the registry and update the current specs to reference it instead of the old aggressive profile. The aggressive thresholds are way too loose compared to v4.3's actual OOS performance of 58.48% annual return with 9.05% max drawdown, so I should tighten the paper trading thresholds accordingly rather than using the legacy 30/35 values. The real issue is that v4_3 isn't registered in the config at all, so it's falling back to the defensive defaults of 10/15, which is way too conservative for this strategy. I need to add the v4_3 profile with thresholds that actually match its risk profile—something like 25% riskoff and 30% halt would be more appropriate given the 23.31% historical drawdown.\n\nActually, stepping back, the user's point about not halting based on max drawdown makes sense. A paper portfolio that's been running since March 17 with real positions should be evaluated on its actual performance, not an arbitrary threshold. The real problem is that v4_3 has no trading history yet since it started today, so I can't compute a meaningful paper-specific drawdown—the fallback to live system's 23.31% is misleading when the portfolio hasn't actually traded.\n\nThe fix is straightforward: add v4_3 to the registry with thresholds that reflect its actual risk profile, and use the live system's OOS max drawdown as a fallback only until real trading data becomes available. For v4_3 specifically, I should set conservative thresholds like 30% riskoff and 35% halt to avoid premature halts while still protecting against extreme drawdowns. The issue is that `get_paper_real_drawdown()` is returning None for v4_3, so it falls back to the live system's 23.31% drawdown, which exceeds the 10.0 threshold and triggers halt. The real problem is that v4_3 isn't registered in the panel config, so it's using defensive thresholds that are too tight for this profile. I need to add v4_3 to the profile registry and set appropriate thresholds that distinguish between current drawdown (which should halt) and historical maximum drawdown (which shouldn't). I need to find where this metric is actually computed in the live trading system to understand what 23.31% represents—whether it's truly an 11-year backtest result or something from a different calculation.","thinkingSignature":"14434bda20ce93e4946e3f4d9bdebb0f268d26fa42a05ab8b38b019ab2443fb0"},{"type":"text","text":"现在我完全理解问题了。需要做两件事：\n\n1. **v4.3 未注册进 panel_profile_registry** → 用的是防御级阈值（10%/15%），而 OOS 回测最大回撤 23.31% 直接超过了这个阈值\n2. **v4.3 今天第一天运行，没有 metrics 文件** → 回退到 live_system 的 11 年回测 OOS 数据（23.31%），这不反映纸盘真实状态\n\n让我看完整注册结构，然后修：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mmgewmokivd2_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/panel_profile_registry.py","offset":1,"limit":155}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49451,"output":1357,"cacheRead":23779,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74587,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775554711434,"responseId":"062403972ef3cdde59f8f00f96937962"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7e844711","parentId":"1700a8b6","timestamp":"2026-04-07T09:39:11.887Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_mmgewmokivd2_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom typing import Any\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Panel-level runtime risk truth configuration\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# 三盘重构核心：每盘使用独立的 runtime risk truth source，不再共享全局 halt。\n# 关键字段说明：\n#   strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct : 本盘允许的最大回撤阈值（触发 risk_off）\n#   strategy_max_drawdown_halt_pct    : 本盘的硬停阈值（触发 halt_new_buy）\n#   halt_gate_source                   : 本盘的 halt gate 来源文件路径模板\n#   candidate_source_tag               : 本盘使用的候选股来源标签\n#   probe_budget_tag                   : 本盘使用的探测预算标签\n#\n# 当前全局风险真相（20260331）：strategy_max_drawdown_pct=24.51%，halt_new_buy=true\n# 三盘分层目标（首轮）：\n#   aggressive : strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct=30%, halt_pct=35%  （容忍最高回撤）\n#   balanced   : strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct=22%, halt_pct=28%\n#   defensive  : strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct=10%, halt_pct=15%  （与原全局一致）\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nPROFILE_RUNTIME_RISK_CONFIG: dict[str, dict[str, Any]] = {\n    \"aggressive\": {\n        \"strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct\": 30.0,\n        \"strategy_max_drawdown_halt_pct\": 35.0,\n        \"halt_gate_source\": \"runtime_risk_state_latest_aggressive.json\",\n        \"candidate_source_tag\": \"aggressive_high_elasticity\",\n        \"probe_budget_tag\": \"probe_budget_high\",\n        \"risk_off_exposure_cap\": 0.85,\n        \"hard_stop_enabled\": True,\n    },\n    \"balanced\": {\n        \"strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct\": 22.0,\n        \"strategy_max_drawdown_halt_pct\": 28.0,\n        \"halt_gate_source\": \"runtime_risk_state_latest_balanced.json\",\n        \"candidate_source_tag\": \"balanced_mid_quality\",\n        \"probe_budget_tag\": \"probe_budget_mid\",\n        \"risk_off_exposure_cap\": 0.70,\n        \"hard_stop_enabled\": True,\n    },\n    \"defensive\": {\n        \"strategy_max_drawdown_riskoff_pct\": 10.0,\n        \"strategy_max_drawdown_halt_pct\": 15.0,\n        \"halt_gate_source\": \"runtime_risk_state_latest_defensive.json\",\n        \"candidate_source_tag\": \"defensive_top_quality\",\n        \"probe_budget_tag\": \"probe_budget_low\",\n        \"risk_off_exposure_cap\": 0.55,\n        \"hard_stop_enabled\": True,\n    },\n}\n\n\ndef profile_runtime_risk_config(profile_slug: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Return the panel-level runtime risk config for a given profile slug.\n\n    Returns a copy so callers can mutate without affecting the registry.\n    Falls back to the defensive defaults if the slug is not found.\n    \"\"\"\n    default_cfg = PROFILE_RUNTIME_RISK_CONFIG.get(\"defensive\", {})\n    return dict(PROFILE_RUNTIME_RISK_CONFIG.get(profile_slug, default_cfg))\n\n\ndef is_panel_level_risk_enabled(profile_slug: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Return True if this profile uses the new panel-level runtime risk truth.\"\"\"\n    return profile_slug in PROFILE_RUNTIME_RISK_CONFIG\n\n\nCURRENT_PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS: list[dict[str, Any]] = [\n    {\n        \"slug\": \"exit_dual\",\n        \"name\": \"双阈退出验证盘（paper_exit_dual）\",\n        \"short_name\": \"双阈退出验证盘\",\n        \"group\": \"exit_validation\",\n        \"group_label\": \"退出实验/失效盘\",\n    },\n    {\n        \"slug\": \"exit_tight\",\n        \"name\": \"紧阈退出验证盘（paper_exit_tight）\",\n        \"short_name\": \"紧阈退出验证盘\",\n        \"group\": \"exit_validation\",\n        \"group_label\": \"退出实验/失效盘\",\n    },\n    {\n        \"slug\": \"alpha55\",\n        \"name\": \"Alpha55 纸盘（paper_alpha55）\",\n        \"short_name\": \"Alpha55 纸盘\",\n        \"group\": \"current_paper\",\n        \"group_label\": \"当前有效纸盘\",\n    },\n]\n\nLEGACY_PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS: list[dict[str, Any]] = [\n    {\n        \"slug\": \"defensive\",\n        \"name\": \"保守纸盘（paper_defensive）\",\n        \"short_name\": \"保守纸盘\",\n        \"group\": \"legacy_paper\",\n        \"group_label\": \"历史兼容纸盘\",\n    },\n    {\n        \"slug\": \"balanced\",\n        \"name\": \"均衡纸盘（paper_balanced）\",\n        \"short_name\": \"均衡纸盘\",\n        \"group\": \"legacy_paper\",\n        \"group_label\": \"历史兼容纸盘\",\n    },\n    {\n        \"slug\": \"aggressive\",\n        \"name\": \"进取纸盘（paper_aggressive）\",\n        \"short_name\": \"进取纸盘\",\n        \"group\": \"legacy_paper\",\n        \"group_label\": \"历史兼容纸盘\",\n    },\n]\n\nBREADTH_PROFILE_SPECS: list[dict[str, Any]] = [\n    {\n        \"slug\": \"breadth_strict_oos\",\n        \"name\": \"严格样本外宽度盘（breadth_strict_oos）\",\n        \"short_name\": \"严格样本外宽度盘\",\n        \"group\": \"breadth_experimental\",\n        \"group_label\": \"宽度实验盘\",\n    },\n    {\n        \"slug\": \"breadth_aggressive\",\n        \"name\": \"进取宽度独立盘（breadth_aggressive）\",\n        \"short_name\": \"进取宽度独立盘\",\n        \"group\": \"breadth_experimental\",\n        \"group_label\": \"宽度实验盘\",\n    },\n]\n\nPAPER_PROFILE_SPECS: list[dict[str, Any]] = CURRENT_PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS + LEGACY_PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS\nALL_STRATEGY_PROFILE_SPECS: list[dict[str, Any]] = PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS + BREADTH_PROFILE_SPECS\n\nCURRENT_PAPER_SLUGS = {item[\"slug\"] for item in CURRENT_PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS}\nLEGACY_PAPER_SLUGS = {item[\"slug\"] for item in LEGACY_PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS}\nBREADTH_SLUGS = {item[\"slug\"] for item in BREADTH_PROFILE_SPECS}\n\nGROUP_ORDER = {\n    \"current_paper\": 0,\n    \"exit_validation\": 1,\n    \"breadth_experimental\": 2,\n    \"legacy_paper\": 3,\n}\n\n\ndef strategy_profile_spec(slug: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    for item in ALL_STRATEGY_PROFILE_SPECS:\n        if item[\"slug\"] == slug:\n            return item\n    return {\n        \"slug\": slug,\n        \"name\": slug,\n\n[5 more lines in file. Use offset=156 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775554751883}}
{"type":"message","id":"21a44016","parentId":"7e844711","timestamp":"2026-04-07T09:39:43.982Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. The fix requires:\n\n1. Add `smallcap_chip_v4_3_aggressive` to `PROFILE_RUNTIME_RISK_CONFIG` with appropriate thresholds (30%/35% to match the aggressive profile, since v4.3 is also an aggressive strategy)\n\n2. Add `smallcap_chip_v4_3_aggressive` to `CURRENT_PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS`\n\n3. Also need to think about the \"first day, no metrics file\" issue. For a brand new paper profile that just started, if there's no metrics file, the `get_paper_real_drawdown()` returns None and it falls back to the live_system's OOS max drawdown. \n\nFor a new profile with no trading history yet, falling back to the live system's drawdown doesn't make sense—the fresh capital should have zero drawdown until positions are actually established. I should also check if `PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS` needs to include this new profile.\n\nLooking at the config, `PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS` combines `CURRENT_PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS` and `LEGACY_PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS`, so adding `smallcap_chip_v4_3_aggressive` to `CURRENT_PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS` will automatically include it in the combined list. For the thresholds, I need to think about what makes sense for this aggressive momentum strategy with a 58.48% OOS Sharpe ratio.\n\nThe issue is that using the live system's 23.31% drawdown as a fallback for a brand new paper account doesn't make sense—the paper should start at 0% since there's no trading history yet. I'm weighing two approaches: either set the thresholds high enough (35%/40%) so the live system's drawdown won't trigger them anyway, or modify the logic to return 0% drawdown for new profiles that have never traded.\n\nThe cleanest solution is option A—just set thresholds at 35%/40% and add the v4.3 profile to the registry. This sidesteps the problem without changing the core logic, though it does mean using the live system's OOS drawdown as a proxy until real paper data exists. But that's actually fine since v4.3's historical max drawdown of 23.31% is below both thresholds anyway, so it won't trigger a halt.\n\nThe real issue is that the defensive fallback uses 10%/15%, which is too strict for a new profile. I need to add the v4.3 profile with aggressive thresholds (30%/35%) and register it in CURRENT_PAPER_PROFILE_SPECS. I should also consider what happens on day one without a metrics file—the fallback to live_system's OOS data (23.31%) is acceptable since it's below the halt threshold, so the paper should start trading unhalted. The concern about this being the \"old\" strategy's drawdown doesn't matter if v4.3 hasn't deviated significantly from it yet.\n\nActually, I'm second-guessing whether using live_system's OOS max drawdown as a proxy for a new paper profile is the right approach. The live_system data represents the old Qlib breadth + turnover strategy, not necessarily what v4.3 will experience. But for a brand new paper on day one with no positions yet, 0% is the most logical choice—the profile started today with fresh capital, so there's been no drawdown to measure.\n\nI could modify `get_paper_real_drawdown` to return 0% when no metrics file exists yet, but that feels semantically wrong since None means \"no data available\" not \"0% drawdown.\" A cleaner approach might be to add a separate field tracking whether the profile has actually started trading, or modify the metrics loading itself to handle the first-day case. Though that's more involved than I want to tackle right now. For v4.3 specifically, the real question is whether the current approach is blocking legitimate trading.\n\nLooking at the numbers, with thresholds at 30%/35% and live_system OOS max drawdown at 23.31%, the halt shouldn't trigger at all. So the immediate fix—adding the profile to the registry and bumping the thresholds—should work, and I can tackle the first-day metrics issue separately. Before I commit to this, I should verify that `smallcap_chip_v4_3_aggressive` is actually the right slug name, and check how the paper_live_trading_v4_3_v1.json config gets loaded to make sure my changes will actually take effect.","thinkingSignature":"6002adf116c8ed06e12a49e5776decd3ad86fd8a67fbc8ee493971568ea5f492"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bh828pv8hdor_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"smallcap_chip_v4_3\\|profile.*slug\\|slug.*=\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_paper_trading_profiles_auto_v1.sh 2>/dev/null | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bh828pv8hdor_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"paper_live_trading_v4_3\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_paper_trading_profiles_auto_v1.sh 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":52347,"output":1083,"cacheRead":23779,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77209,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775554751888,"responseId":"062403c0991a98b96072e09e08ca7973"}}
