{"type":"message","id":"3bda3c33","parentId":"909737bd","timestamp":"2026-04-07T09:40:59.292Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now let me run the paper trading refresh again to verify the fix works. The key change is that v4_3_aggressive now uses riskoff_pct=30% and halt_pct=35%, so the 23.31% OOS drawdown won't trigger halt.\n\nBut wait - I realize there's another important issue. The paper trading for v4_3_aggressive is using `get_paper_real_drawdown()` which looks for `paper_v4_3_aggressive_trading_metrics_*.json`. But the metrics file name uses the config's `profile_slug` which is `v4_3_aggressive`. \n\nI need to verify what the actual metrics filename format is - it might be `paper_v4_3_aggressive_trading_metrics_20260407.json` or something like `paper_smallcap_momentum_chip_v4_3_trading_metrics_*.json` depending on how the slug maps to the filename. Looking at the existing files like `paper_aggressive_trading_metrics_*.json`, the pattern seems to use the slug directly, so for v4_3_aggressive it would be `paper_v4_3_aggressive_trading_metrics_*.json`.\n\nThe config's profile_name is \"小市值筹码v4.3进取型\" which is different from the slug, so I need to trace through how the metrics filename gets constructed from the profile configuration.\n\nSince the metrics file is dated today (20260407), it probably won't exist until the end of day when the paper trading dashboard runs and generates it. The real issue is that `get_paper_real_drawdown()` is trying to load today's metrics file, but it won't be available yet since we're running this in the morning.\n\nLet me test the paper trading refresh with the new configuration to confirm the halt logic is working correctly with the updated thresholds, though I should be mindful that it might take some time to complete.","thinkingSignature":"540be1109c67e11abffdbfc7c4a1ea48f609afce8a7de7fc1daecfc677fb62b0"},{"type":"text","text":"好，配置文件更新完成，语法也正确。现在重新跑模拟盘刷新验证修复效果：\n"},{"type":"toolCall