{"type":"message","id":"510e402d","parentId":"16ed2dde","timestamp":"2026-04-07T09:41:44.203Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1smmzsdniqtz_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nROOT=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\" && pwd)\"\nWORKSPACE_ROOT=\"$(cd \"$ROOT/../..\" && pwd)\"\nPYRUN=\"$ROOT/scripts/cron_python.sh\"\nREPORT_DIR=\"$ROOT/research/reports\"\nexport REPORT_DIR\ncd \"$ROOT\"\n\n# shellcheck disable=SC1091\nsource \"$ROOT/scripts/source_optional_env.sh\"\n\nexport LITELLM_LOCAL_MODEL_COST_MAP=true\n\"$PYRUN\" --runtime-only\n\nfor ENV_FILE in \\\n  \"$ROOT/.env.tushare\" \\\n  \"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/.env.tushare\"\ndo\n  source_optional_env_file \"$ENV_FILE\"\ndone\n\nDATE_TAG=\"${1:-$(date +%Y%m%d)}\"\nTICKETS_FILE=\"${2:-}\"\nRUN_MODE=\"${3:-${PAPER_PROFILE_RUN_MODE:-eod}}\"\nRETRY_MAX=\"${PAPER_PROFILES_RETRY_MAX:-2}\"\nRETRY_SLEEP_SEC=\"${PAPER_PROFILES_RETRY_SLEEP_SEC:-5}\"\nLIVE_SCHEDULER_CFG=\"$ROOT/config/live_scheduler_v1.json\"\nTODAY_TAG=\"$(date +%Y%m%d)\"\nLIVE_SYSTEM_FILE=\"$ROOT/research/reports/live_system_v1_${DATE_TAG}.json\"\nMERGED_FILE=\"$ROOT/signals/merged/merged_signals_${DATE_TAG}.csv\"\n\ncheck_runtime_halt_before_profiles() {\n  local runtime_file=\"$REPORT_DIR/runtime_risk_state_latest.json\"\n  if [[ ! -f \"$runtime_file\" ]]; then\n    return 0\n  fi\n  local halt\n  halt=\"$(\"$PYRUN\" --no-runtime-log - \"$runtime_file\" \"$DATE_TAG\" <<'PY2'\nimport json, sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\np = Path(sys.argv[1])\ndate_tag = sys.argv[2]\nobj = json.loads(p.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\nlatest = obj.get(\"latest_runtime\") or {}\nif str(obj.get(\"date_tag\") or \"\") != str(date_tag):\n    print(\"0\")\nelse:\n    print(\"1\" if latest.get(\"halt_new_buy\") else \"0\")\nPY2\n)\"\n  if [[ \"$halt\" == \"1\" ]]; then\n    echo \"[BLOCK] runtime halt_new_buy=true; skip paper profile execution before account write\"\n    return 2\n  fi\n  return 0\n}\n\nread_live_sizing() {\n  \"$PYRUN\" --no-runtime-log - \"$LIVE_SCHEDULER_CFG\" <<'PY'\nimport json\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\ncfg_path = Path(sys.argv[1])\npayload = json.loads(cfg_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")) if cfg_path.exists() else {}\nprint(payload.get(\"available_cash\", 1000000))\nprint(payload.get(\"account_nav\", payload.get(\"available_cash\", 1000000)))\nPY\n}\n\nensure_same_day_merged_signals() {\n  local sizing available_cash account_nav force_flag=\"\"\n  sizing=\"$(read_live_sizing)\"\n  available_cash=\"$(printf '%s\\n' \"$sizing\" | sed -n '1p')\"\n  account_nav=\"$(printf '%s\\n' \"$sizing\" | sed -n '2p')\"\n  if [[ \"${FORCE_REFRESH:-0}\" == \"1\" ]]; then\n    force_flag=\"--force-rebuild\"\n    echo \"[INFO] force rebuilding same-day merged signals date=${DATE_TAG}\"\n\n[74 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775554904198}}
{"type":"message","id":"548aabc0","parentId":"510e402d","timestamp":"2026-04-07T09:42:09.250Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue more clearly. The `check_runtime_halt_before_profiles()` function checks the global `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` and if `halt_new_buy=true`, it skips the paper profile execution entirely.\n\nThe global `halt_new_buy=true` comes from the live trading system's risk state, which includes `strategy_max_drawdown_pct(23.31%) >= 10.0000`. This is the issue the user is complaining about.\n\nBut wait - this is the **global** halt check, not the per-panel halt check. Even if we fix the per-panel v4_3 thresholds, this global check would still block the paper trading from running.\n \nSo there are actually two separate problems here. The user's point about not halting new positions just because of max drawdown is valid - that's a historical metric, not a current risk measure. But there's also this global halt blocking the paper profiles entirely. Looking at where `check_runtime_halt_before_profiles()` gets called in the auto script, if it returns 2, the whole paper trading pipeline stops. Yet I know other profiles like aggressive and balanced are somehow running despite this global block.\n\nThe `cron_paper_trading_profiles_v1.sh` script calls the auto version, which has this halt check. So how are those other profiles executing? Maybe they're not actually running today, or maybe I'm misunderstanding where this check is enforced. Let me trace through the first run output more carefully - it shows the status as PASS and mentions attempting paper_profiles, so something is actually happening.\n\nLooking at the second run with the halt applied, it shows `halt_new_buy=true` with a skip message. This suggests the halt is being triggered in the second run but not the first, which is why the first run appears to succeed and the second one gets blocked.\n\nThe real issue is understanding the order of operations in the cron script. It seems like `cron_paper_trading_profiles_v1.sh` runs the risk rechecks first to generate `runtime_risk_state_latest.json`, and then `run_paper_trading_profiles_auto_v1.sh` reads from that file to decide whether to halt. So the first execution might not have the halt flag set yet, but once the risk state is updated with `halt_new_buy=true`, subsequent runs in the same day would see that flag and skip the paper trading step.\n\nBut if aggressive is running today despite the halt, it means either the halt check is passing for some reason, or the profiles are running through a different execution path that doesn't go through the auto wrapper. I need to trace through how the profiles actually get invoked to understand why they're still executing when they should be blocked. The real problem is that the halt logic is incorrectly using historical maximum drawdown to block new positions—when the live system hits a new equity low, that historical metric spikes and stops everything, even though the actual current drawdown might be fine. This global gate is too blunt an instrument. For the paper trading specifically, the issue is that v4_3 isn't registered in the per-panel config, so it's falling back to defensive thresholds that are overly restrictive. I need to focus on clarifying whether the global halt is what's blocking paper execution, or if it's the per-panel thresholds, and then address whichever is the actual constraint.","thinkingSignature":"f9567b76e9c81d4da0658c5a407dba1bc5baa11c3bb640d9c37ac72ce88c038a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z2l6sowrf1zl_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"check_runtime_halt\\|halt_before\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_paper_trading_profiles_auto_v1.sh 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":60044,"output":756,"cacheRead":23779,"cacheWrit