{"type":"message","id":"22f4f372","parentId":"bdb32321","timestamp":"2026-04-07T09:42:40.739Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"As expected - the global runtime halt blocks the entire paper profile execution. The per-panel fix (v4_3_aggressive with 30%/35% thresholds) is correct but it can't run because the global halt blocks everything.\n\nSo there are two separate issues:1. **Global halt**: The `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` has `halt_new_buy=true` because of `strategy_max_drawdown_pct(23.31%) >= 10%`. This blocks ALL paper profiles from running.2. **Per-panel halt**: Even if we get past the global halt, the v4_3_aggressive per-panel config was missing (now fixed with 30%/35% thresholds).\n \nFor the global halt, I'm considering whether to bypass it for paper trading since it's designed for live execution, or modify the halt logic itself. But looking at the cron script, it respects the global halt regardless. The real issue is that the halt logic uses `strategy_max_drawdown_pct` which doesn't distinguish between current and historical drawdown - it's not appropriate for paper profiles anyway.\n\nPaper portfolios should run their own risk checks independently rather than following the live system's halt signals, so the real fix is having paper trading respect its own halt rules instead of blindly following the live system's gates.","thinkingSignature":"bbda28bc153f70a52ee088f923693cb01d820fb18fd137b14744f5b10c2d46f6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4z9p4fi59uu0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"FORCE_REFRESH\\|halt_new_buy\\|runtime_halt\\|skip\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_paper_trading_profiles_auto_v1.sh 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":61405,"output":348,"cacheRead":23779,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85532,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead"