{"type":"message","id":"9175bc79","parentId":"3ad1b810","timestamp":"2026-04-07T12:06:01.217Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to set up the dashboard to update at 4:30 PM on trading days. Looking at the cron setup:\n- The postclose cron runs at \"30 16 * * 1-5\" (4:30 PM on weekdays)\n- The generate_dashboard_portal.py is called in cron_paper_trading_profiles_v1.sh\n\nThe issue is that cron_paper_trading_profiles_v1.sh is the script that runs the paper trading profiles, and it runs at some time. Looking at what I saw earlier:\n- It ran around 16:50 today (after market close)\n- The dashboard was generated at 19:00:04\n\nThe user wants to set up the dashboard to update at 4:30 PM (16:30) on opening days (trading days). \n\nLooking at the cron, there's already a postclose job at 16:30 that runs the background cycle. Maybe the dashboard should be generated as part of that, or as part of the paper trading profiles which runs after market close.\n\nLet me check if there's a dedicated dashboard generation cron or if we need to add one.\n","thinkingSignature":"372847b23eb7d43e24f96bab9626f3e0ad8917f2766b2c5008ac81a0a0d44f47"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_haoea5yp9cmv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"dashboard\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/cron/jobs.json 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":134,"output":285,"cacheRead":87424,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87843,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775563549613,"responseId":"0624261defa7764e4c11b1f4e1ff26bc"}}
