whole module first.\\n\\nWait... but the error said `name 'compute_candidate_snapshot' is not defined`. \\n\\nOh, I see the actual problem now. The `compute_candidate_snapshot` function is defined after `if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":` at line 612, but `main()` is called at line 671 inside that block. When Python parses the file, it executes code sequentially, so `main()` gets called before the function at line 612 is ever defined.\\n\\nActually, wait - that's not how Python works. All function definitions get parsed first regardless of order, so `compute_candidate_snapshot` should be available to `main()` even though it appears later in the file. Let me reconsider what's actually happening here.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_function_oqrz6ugveekz_1\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"python3 -m py_compile ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_live_smallcap_candidates.py && echo \\\"Syntax OK\\\"\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"minimax-portal\",\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775554650072,\n      \"responseId\": \"0624035a805215bd133e02eb92d634dd\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"0af0b054\",\n        \"seq\": 708\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Ah, there's a syntax error! The `snap_file.write_text(json.dumps(snapshot, ensure_ascii=False) + \\\"\\\\n\\\")` line got mangled. The `\\\\n` at the end of the heredoc in the original `cat >>` command was interpreted as a newline by the shell. Let me look at what's happening at line 643.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_function_mz98108b25qz_1\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"sed -n '638,650p' ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_live_smallcap_candidates.py\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"minimax-portal\",\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775554660691,\n      \"responseId\": \"062403652f981e9417c0002d4748155d\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"1c37a056\",\n        \"seq\": 710\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Line 644 has a syntax error. The `\\\"+\\\"` line is broken - the string continuation got split. It should be:\\n```python\\nsnap_file.write_text(json.dumps(snapshot, ensure_ascii=False) + \\\"\\\\n\\\", encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\")\\n```\\n\\nBut it got written as:\\n```python\\nsnap_file.write_text(json.dumps(snapshot, ensure_ascii=False) + \\\"\\n\\\", encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\")\\n```\\n\\nThe `\\\"\\\\n\\\"` from the heredoc was interpreted as an actual newline, splitting the string. Let me fix this.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"\\n语法错误——heredoc 的 `\\\\n` 被当成真实换行符了。修复：\\n\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_function_eydorocl1qrl_1\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"python3 - << 'PYEOF'\\npath = \\\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_live_smallcap_candidates.py\\\"\\nwith open(path) as f:\\n    content = f.read()\\n\\n# Fix the broken string continuation in save_snapshot\\nold = 'snap_file.write_text(json.dumps(snapshot, ensure_ascii=False) + \\\"\\\\n\\\"'\\nfixed = 'snap_file.write_text(json.dumps(snapshot, ensure_ascii=False) + \\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\"'\\ncontent = content.replace(\\n    'snap_file.write_text(json.dumps(snapshot, ensure_ascii=False) + \\\"\\\\n\\\"',\\n    'snap_file.write_text(json.dumps(snapshot, ensure_ascii=False) + \\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\"'\\n)\\n# Also fix the one that was split across lines\\ncontent = content.replace(\\n    'snap_file.write_text(json.dumps(snapshot, ensure_ascii=False) + \\\"\\\\n\\\", encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\")',\\n    'snap_file.write_text(json.dumps(snapshot, ensure_ascii=False) + \\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\", encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\")'\\n)\\nwith open(path, \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n    f.write(content)\\nprint(\\\"Fixed\\\")\\nPYEOF\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"minimax-portal\",\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775554665355,\n      \"responseId\": \"06240369d43c0675a6be86b166479f99\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"58ea57c4\",\n        \"seq\": 712\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Let me verify the fix and check syntax.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_function_nikzvbjjp9a8_1\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"python3 -m py_compile ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_live_smallcap_candidates.py && echo \\\"Syntax OK\\\"\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"provider\": \"minimax-portal\",\n      \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1775554675441,\n      \"responseId\": \"0624037390e0e76701fff47a15cd084d\",\n      \"__openclaw\": {\n        \"id\": \"25c413e6\",\n        \"seq\": 714\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"ty