{"type":"message","id":"ebc2cf85","parentId":"71427ad1","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:28:51.326Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8ofgqkp1r1ii_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.5 (3e72c03) — Greetings, Professor Falken\n\nUsage: openclaw message send [options]\n\nSend a message\n\nOptions:\n  --account <id>         Channel account id (accountId)\n  --buttons <json>       Telegram inline keyboard buttons as JSON (array of\n                         button rows)\n  --card <json>          Adaptive Card JSON object (when supported by the\n                         channel)\n  --channel <channel>    Channel:\n                         feishu|googlechat|nostr|msteams|mattermost|nextcloud-talk|matrix|bluebubbles|line|zalo|zalouser|synology-chat|tlon|qa-channel|discord|imessage|irc|qqbot|signal|slack|telegram|twitch|whatsapp\n  --components <json>    Discord components payload as JSON\n  --dry-run              Print payload and skip sending (default: false)\n  --force-document       Send media as document to avoid Telegram compression\n                         (Telegram only). Applies to images and GIFs. (default:\n                         false)\n  --gif-playback         Treat video media as GIF playback (WhatsApp only).\n                         (default: false)\n  -h, --help             Display help for command\n  --interactive <json>   Shared interactive payload as JSON (buttons/selects\n                         rendered natively by supported channels)\n  --json                 Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>   Message body (required unless --media is set)\n  --media <path-or-url>  Attach media (image/audio/video/document). Accepts\n                         local paths or URLs.\n  --reply-to <id>        Reply-to message id"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":8394,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.5 (3e72c03) — Greetings, Professor Falken\n\nUsage: openclaw message send [options]\n\nSend a message\n\nOptions:\n  --account <id>         Channel account id (accountId)\n  --buttons <json>       Telegram inline keyboard buttons as JSON (array of\n                         button rows)\n  --card <json>          Adaptive Card JSON object (when supported by the\n                         channel)\n  --channel <channel>    Channel:\n                         feishu|googlechat|nostr|msteams|mattermost|nextcloud-talk|matrix|bluebubbles|line|zalo|zalouser|synology-chat|tlon|qa-channel|discord|imessage|irc|qqbot|signal|slack|telegram|twitch|whatsapp\n  --components <json>    Discord components payload as JSON\n  --dry-run              Print payload and skip sending (default: false)\n  --force-document       Send media as document to avoid Telegram compression\n                         (Telegram only). Applies to images and GIFs. (default:\n                         false)\n  --gif-playback         Treat video media as GIF playback (WhatsApp only).\n                         (default: false)\n  -h, --help             Display help for command\n  --interactive <json>   Shared interactive payload as JSON (buttons/selects\n                         rendered natively by supported channels)\n  --json                 Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>   Message body (required unless --media is set)\n  --media <path-or-url>  Attach media (image/audio/video/document). Accepts\n                         local paths or URLs.\n  --reply-to <id>        Reply-to message id","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775575731321}}
{"type":"message","id":"379d1fd9","parentId":"ebc2cf85","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:28:59.988Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can use `openclaw message send` command to send the Feishu message. Let me update the push function to use this instead of the direct Feishu API.\n\nThe function should:1. Build the message text2. Call `openclaw message send --channel feishu --target user:ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae --message \"...\"`Let me update the function:\n","thinkingSignature":"2adb9d035b32060ab697c616a1abbcc8ac90bf036626a6943cd5af67a7783c71"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pth2xnyb0uk6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"def _push_candidate_change\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_live_smallcap_candidates.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":835,"output":160,"cacheRead":103424,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104419,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775575731328,"responseId":"062455b37f6befd26513e614d273a0b5"}}
